tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, low total protein, low CO₂, and elevated liver enzymes, suggesting impaired renal function with possible metabolic acidosis and mild hepatic involvement. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with abnormal urine appearance and color, supporting nephrotic syndrome or acute kidney injury with possible underlying diabetes or liver dysfunction. Immediate clinical evaluation and further diagnostic workup are recommended.
